        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>What is HTML?</h2>
                <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard markup language for creating web pages and web applications. It describes the structure of a web page and consists of a series of elements that tell the browser how to display content.</p>
                <p>HTML elements are the building blocks of HTML pages. Each element is represented by tags that label pieces of content such as "heading", "paragraph", "table", and so on.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Why Learn HTML?</h2>
                <p>HTML is the foundation of all web pages. Without HTML, you wouldn't be able to organize text or add images and videos to your web pages.</p>
                <p>Learning HTML is the first step in web development and essential for:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Building websites</li>
                    <li>Web development careers</li>
                    <li>Content management</li>
                    <li>Digital marketing</li>
                    <li>Blogging</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Key HTML Features</h2>
